OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FKatty Kay: The most        
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fexciting thing about       
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fbecoming Swiss             
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Last year I became a Swiss citizen. It 
OL,6, was a three-year battle of will (mine) 
OL,7, over bureaucracy (theirs). I won. I    
OL,8, have my grandmother to thank.          
OL,10,FI now have an elegant Swiss passport,  
OL,11,Fthe right to live anywhere in Europe,  
OL,12,Fthe theoretical chance to buy property 
OL,13,Fin Switzerland and, more exciting than 
OL,14,Fany of that, I have the right to vote. 
OL,16,FI haven't voted in almost two decades. 
OL,17,FI'm British but I have lived abroad so 
OL,18,Flong that I lost my right to vote in   
OL,19,Fthe UK. I'm not American, so I can't   
OL,20,Fvote in the country I live in. For     
OL,21,Fyears I've been disenfranchised.       
